The paper deals with the state complexity of regular languages, which is a topic in formal language theory (FL). The focus is on nondeterministic finite-state automata (DS), which are commonly used to recognize regular languages. The paper establishes upper and lower bounds for basic operations on regular languages, which is a topic in computational complexity (CC). The paper also uses techniques from combinatorics (LO) and information theory (IT) to establish these bounds.
